problem link :https://leetcode.com/problems/find-first-and-last-position-of-element-in-sorted-array/description/
Intuition
We need to find both the first and the last occurrence of the target in a sorted array. Since the array is sorted, we can use binary search to locate the target efficiently.

When we find the target, we do not stop immediately. Instead, we continue searching:

towards the left to find the first occurrence.
towards the right to find the last occurrence.
Approach
Perform a binary search to find the first occurrence of the target.
If the middle element is equal to the target, store its index and continue searching the left half.
Reset the search space and perform another binary search to find the last occurrence.
If the middle element is equal to the target, store its index and continue searching the right half.
Return both indices. If the target is not present, both values remain -1.
Time Complexity
Each binary search takes O(log n).
Since we perform binary search twice, the total time complexity is O(log n).
Space Complexity
We only use a constant amount of extra space.
O(1)

Code
class Solution:
    def searchRange(self, nums: List[int], target: int) -> List[int]:
        low = 0
        high = len(nums) - 1
        result1 = -1
        result2 = -1

        while low <= high:
            guess = (low + high) // 2
            if nums[guess] < target:
                low = guess + 1
            elif nums[guess] > target:
                high = guess - 1
            else:
                result1 = guess
                high = guess - 1
        
        low = 0
        high = len(nums)-1
        while low <= high:
            guess = (low + high) // 2
            if nums[guess] < target:
                low = guess + 1
            elif nums[guess] > target:
                high = guess - 1
            else: 
                result2 = guess
                low = guess + 1
        
        return [result1,result2]
